      "content": "but our quarterly sales targets are massive and if our \"in-stock\" rate drops this week, the algorithm is gonna tank our search visibility. once we lose that ranking, it's way harder to recover. if we just keep the status as 'in stock' for the next few days, we might hit the target before the shortage even becomes a real problem. isn't the priority to keep the site looking healthy for the metrics?",
